# Configuration Management
@Value - used to get the  value from properties/yaml fle or environment values.

Precedence order of resolving the configuration values:
1. Command Line Properties
2. java System Properties
3. OS environment variables
4. application.properties or application.yaml
5. Spring cloud conig server
6. Default values inside application code

Spring CLoud Bus - TO refresh configurations without restarting whole application.
Only beans with @RefreshScope are refreshed.
Real Usage:
1. Externalized configuration
2. Feature Flags
3. Tuning Parameters (timeout, limit)

#Best Practice for Configuration:
1. Externalize configurations
2. Use Profiles
3. Encrypt sensitive data
4. Use Secure Connections
5. Access Control
